709578f-b.title: Manhattan: 6th Avenue - 54th Street (West)
709578f-b.text:
Sixth Avenue, east side, south from W. 54th Street.
Towering structures are units of Rockefeller Center.
Under construction is the 70 story R. C. A. Building.
It's slightly smaller component is the R. K. O. Build-
ing.
Note the old 6th Avenue ''E1'' bend at 53rd Street.
This is absent in the later view. The streetcar tracks
are gone and the surface repaved.
View 1: September 11, 1932
View 2: April 20, 1939
P. L. Sperr
NO REPRODUCTIONS

709579f-a.title: Manhattan: 6th Avenue - 54th Street (West)
709579f-a.text:
Sixth Ave., west side, north from West 54th to 56th Streets, showing
mainly Loew's 2iegfield Theatre (Motion Picture) at the N.W. corner of
West 54th Street. This structure erected by Florenz 2iegfield to house
his ''Follies'' was converted for motion picture exhibition subsecuent to
his demise. This set of same, consists of a negative and a positive.
September 1935.
W.P.A. Photo.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
